01:03:33,577 --> 01:03:37,514
You say 
 you committed suicide 
 in 1890,

913
01:03:37,547 --> 01:03:40,550
and yet you're alive today...

914
01:03:40,584 --> 01:03:43,020
Over 100 years later.

915
01:03:43,053 --> 01:03:45,089
How do you explain that?

916
01:03:45,122 --> 01:03:49,493
The beauty of the flowers
is calling me back to life.

917
01:03:49,526 --> 01:03:52,930
- it's part of the spell.
- tell me about the spell.

918
01:03:52,963 --> 01:03:55,900
I swallowed a potato potion...

919
01:03:57,001 --> 01:04:00,004
In 1885,

920
01:04:00,037 --> 01:04:03,941
given to me
 by a kindly peasant woman,
 margot.

921
01:04:05,209 --> 01:04:08,312
She posed for me
 for my painting,

922
01:04:08,345 --> 01:04:10,214
the potato eaters.

923
01:04:10,247 --> 01:04:14,651
[ Margot's voice ] 
 After your body lies dead and 
 still in the cold ground...

924
01:04:14,684 --> 01:04:16,653
For more than a century,

925
01:04:16,686 --> 01:04:20,424
the flowers will summon you
 back among the living,

926
01:04:20,457 --> 01:04:23,093
but only for 100 days.

927
01:04:23,127 --> 01:04:26,563
[ Vincent ] 
 The flowers 
 returned my love...

928
01:04:26,596 --> 01:04:31,168
And brought me 
 back to life here.

929
01:04:31,201 --> 01:04:33,904
Margot said 
 on the hundredth day...

930
01:04:33,938 --> 01:04:36,540
The waves and the sea 
 would take me away.

931
01:04:41,611 --> 01:04:46,083
So, he's a flaming lunatic.
Totally nuts
from top to bottom?

932
01:04:46,116 --> 01:04:49,086
Okay, if that's
 the way you think,
 then stop this crusade...

933
01:04:49,119 --> 01:04:51,088
And let him cop
 to an insanity plea.

934
01:04:51,121 --> 01:04:54,324
That would be
 the biggest mistake the state
 of California ever made.

935
01:04:54,358 --> 01:04:57,061
How so?
 Because he's not insane.

936
01:04:57,094 --> 01:05:00,931
Oh! So now you admit
 he's not insane! Fine.

937
01:05:00,965 --> 01:05:03,500
What are you saying,
 that you disagree
 with Dr. Ruby's diagnosis?

938
01:05:03,533 --> 01:05:06,903
I'm saying I know a lot more
 about this case than Dr. Ruby.

939
01:05:13,343 --> 01:05:15,412
And there it is.

940
01:05:15,445 --> 01:05:20,417
Not quite as nice 
 as my portrait of Dr. Gachet, 
 but you'll do,

941
01:05:20,450 --> 01:05:24,021
and I call you
 portrait of officer goodman.

942
01:05:24,054 --> 01:05:26,423
No one's ever captured me 
 like this before.

943
01:05:26,456 --> 01:05:28,959
It almost looks 
 like a van gogh.

944
01:05:30,327 --> 01:05:32,462
You're not trying
to get me to believe...

945
01:05:32,496 --> 01:05:34,965
That this man is actually
 the real vincent van gogh.

946
01:05:34,999 --> 01:05:37,234
I believe him.

947
01:05:37,267 --> 01:05:39,269
Well, then you've
 lost your mind.

948
01:05:40,504 --> 01:05:43,140
And you have lost
 your heart.
 [ Scoffs ]

949
01:05:43,173 --> 01:05:47,978
Aunt gladys,
 he really is who he says he
 is, and we have to trust him.

950
01:05:48,012 --> 01:05:50,014
You're asking me
to believe in miracles.

951
01:05:50,047 --> 01:05:52,082
Of course. Don't you?

952
01:05:52,116 --> 01:05:55,419
- I've never seen one.
 - yes, you have.

953
01:05:55,452 --> 01:05:58,355
When the doctors told mom
 she couldn't have a baby,
 and then I came along.

954
01:05:58,388 --> 01:06:01,191
Wasn't that a miracle?
 Maybe there's room for two.

955
01:06:01,225 --> 01:06:03,260
Oh, kathy, I--

956
01:06:05,195 --> 01:06:07,164
all right.
 All right.
 Oh--

957
01:06:07,197 --> 01:06:09,766
he can have a show here
in the gallery.

958
01:06:09,799 --> 01:06:12,469
But if the critics hate it,
it comes down the next day.

959
01:06:12,502 --> 01:06:14,771
Oh, I love you!
 [ Laughing ]

960
01:06:14,804 --> 01:06:17,174
Do me a favor,
 will you?

961
01:06:17,207 --> 01:06:19,076
Next time you pick up
 a bum on the street,

962
01:06:19,109 --> 01:06:21,511
don't make your aim so high.

963
01:06:21,545 --> 01:06:24,548
Find some lunatic
 who thinks he's liberace.

964
01:06:24,581 --> 01:06:26,716
Okay.

965
01:06:26,750 --> 01:06:28,552
[ Male newscaster ] 
 Almost six weeks ago...

966
01:06:28,585 --> 01:06:31,088
That man who calls himself 
 vincent van gogh...

967
01:06:31,121 --> 01:06:34,091
Walked into an auction 
 and created 
 an unbelievable spectacle...

968
01:06:34,124 --> 01:06:37,627
That ended up with him in 
 jail, where he is 
 now awaiting trial.

969
01:06:37,661 --> 01:06:41,098
The question is, 
 is this strange prisoner 
 a con man...

970
01:06:41,131 --> 01:06:43,567
An impostor,
 or much worse?

971
01:06:43,600 --> 01:06:45,735
Well, not everyone
 is betting on worse.

972
01:06:45,769 --> 01:06:48,372
In fact,
 tonight from New York,
 we have a report...

973
01:06:48,405 --> 01:06:53,277
That the controversial
 publisher may be ready to come
 up with a six-figure advance

974
01:06:53,310 --> 01:06:56,646
For the autobiography of the
 man who claims to be vincent.

975
01:06:56,680 --> 01:06:59,083
That could mean the man
 would be out on bail.

976
01:06:59,116 --> 01:07:01,285
Gabe insisted
 on picking you up.

977
01:07:01,318 --> 01:07:04,654
We have some
 celebrating to do.
 Gabe!

978
01:07:04,688 --> 01:07:06,623
[ Laughing ]

979
01:07:06,656 --> 01:07:10,094
Oh. Thank you
 for getting me out of there.

980
01:07:10,127 --> 01:07:13,397
How can I ever repay you?
 I've got some ideas
 on that, vince baby.

981
01:07:13,430 --> 01:07:16,200
Now, remember, you're just
 out on bail until trial,

982
01:07:16,233 --> 01:07:18,068
so don't let it
 go to your head.

983
01:07:18,102 --> 01:07:20,637
You are hot as a pistol.

984
01:07:20,670 --> 01:07:24,241
I just landed a deal
for your autobiography.

985
01:07:24,274 --> 01:07:28,245
We, uh-- we spent 
 the six-figure advance 
 to get you out on bail.

986
01:07:28,278 --> 01:07:30,247
So now you're gonna
 have to become a writer.

987
01:07:30,280 --> 01:07:32,849
A writer, gabe?
 I don't know about that.

988
01:07:32,882 --> 01:07:36,253
I wrote to my brother theo
 many letters, yes,
 but a book?

989
01:07:36,286 --> 01:07:39,356
Chill out.
We'll get a ghostwriter
from New York.

990
01:07:39,389 --> 01:07:42,692
They're a dime a dozen. 
 Come on. Get in.

991
01:07:47,197 --> 01:07:49,499
Oh, and, vincent,
 I talked my aunt...

992
01:07:49,533 --> 01:07:51,435
Into holding an exhibition
 of your new paintings.

993
01:07:51,468 --> 01:07:54,671
She's even inviting
 some well-known
 west coast critics.

994
01:07:54,704 --> 01:07:56,806
Whoo-hoo-hoo,
 whoo-hoo-hoo!

995
01:07:56,840 --> 01:07:59,609
[ Gabe ] hold on 
 to your hat, vince! 
 Whoo!

996
01:07:59,643 --> 01:08:04,448
Now, see? This.
It has your personality
written all over it.

997
01:08:04,481 --> 01:08:07,484
It does.
 And see how nicely
 it goes with this jacket?

998
01:08:07,517 --> 01:08:09,653
Mm. Okay.
Mm-hmm.

999
01:08:09,686 --> 01:08:13,423
Before I'm finished with you,
 you're going to be
 a fashion trendsetter.

1000
01:08:13,457 --> 01:08:18,128
Kathy, I've decided
 how to thank aunt gladys
 for giving me my show.

1001
01:08:18,162 --> 01:08:21,431
I'm going
 to make her a gift of one
 of my Hollywood paintings.

1002
01:08:21,465 --> 01:08:24,568
She'll love that.
 Okay. Come on.
 Into the dressing room.

1003
01:08:24,601 --> 01:08:27,237
In you go.
 In we go.

1004
01:08:29,239 --> 01:08:32,742
I think I'll give her 
 one of my harley-davidson 
 hell angels paintings.

1005
01:08:32,776 --> 01:08:34,744
I hope she likes 
 the large ones.

1006
01:08:34,778 --> 01:08:36,913
She can do anything 
 with it she likes,

1007
01:08:36,946 --> 01:08:40,284
as long as 
 it doesn't end up 
 in a chicken coop.

1008
01:08:40,317 --> 01:08:42,752
Why would anybody
 put a painting
 in a chicken coop?

1009
01:08:42,786 --> 01:08:46,256
Well, when I painted 
 a portrait of one 
 of my doctors--

1010
01:08:46,290 --> 01:08:51,695
I'm talking about 
 Dr. Felix rey, a swine 
 if ever I did know one--

1011
01:08:51,728 --> 01:08:55,165
anyway, he hated it 
 so much, he hung it up 
 in his chicken coop...

1012
01:08:55,199 --> 01:08:57,401
To hide a hole 
 in the wall!

1013
01:09:10,614 --> 01:09:12,782
I have with me 
 lester finley,

1014
01:09:12,816 --> 01:09:15,352
art critic
for the Los Angeles times.

1015
01:09:15,385 --> 01:09:18,722
How are you
 this evening, lester?
 I'm fine, maria, just fine.

1016
01:09:18,755 --> 01:09:21,758
Well, lester,
 what's your verdict?
 I wish I could be kind, maria,

1017
01:09:21,791 --> 01:09:24,761
but critics have
 a responsibility
 to the public.

1018
01:09:24,794 --> 01:09:28,332
I describe this exhibit
 in one WORD:
 Very disappointing.

1019
01:09:28,365 --> 01:09:30,834
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.
 And, lester, why
 do you say that?

1020
01:09:30,867 --> 01:09:34,304
After all the controversy
 over who this artist is,

1021
01:09:34,338 --> 01:09:37,607
one thing for sure,
 he's not vincent van gogh.

1022
01:09:37,641 --> 01:09:39,643
This is nothing
 but an amateurish attempt...

1023
01:09:39,676 --> 01:09:44,914
To imitate post-impressionism
 and apply it to our modern age

1024
01:09:44,948 --> 01:09:46,916
where it has
 absolutely no place.

1025
01:09:46,950 --> 01:09:48,785
Thank you, lester.
 Thank you.

1026
01:09:48,818 --> 01:09:53,623
[ Maria ] We have with us 
 sarah centurion, critic for 
 art world magazine.

1027
01:09:53,657 --> 01:09:57,461
-What do you say about vincent 
-Juvenile in his
message, maria.

1028
01:09:57,494 --> 01:10:00,764
No interest in it 
 in our contemporary 
 art scene,

1029
01:10:00,797 --> 01:10:03,967
and that is
 the nicest way
 I can say it.

1030
01:10:04,000 --> 01:10:06,303
Well, sarah, thank you
 for your honesty.

1031
01:10:08,238 --> 01:10:12,742
[ Man ] this is a charade. 
 It's a mockery of everything 
 tat vincent van gogh held dear

1032
01:10:12,776 --> 01:10:15,011
So, ted,
 in a nutshell?

1033
01:10:15,044 --> 01:10:18,848
This is all
 worthless trash.

1034
01:10:22,051 --> 01:10:24,788
Taking a few
 tough punches tonight,
 huh, vincent?

1035
01:10:24,821 --> 01:10:27,957
I'm used to not being liked
 by the critics.

1036
01:10:27,991 --> 01:10:31,495
Maybe the jig is up;
 maybe youre gona find out that
 you can't bamboozle everybody-

1037
01:10:31,528 --> 01:10:33,563
that there's a lot
 of us here who love art...

1038
01:10:33,597 --> 01:10:37,334
And love van gogh enough
 to put you in your place.

1039
01:10:37,367 --> 01:10:41,538
If that were true--
 about the love-- I think you'd
 show me a little more respect.

1040
01:10:41,571 --> 01:10:46,576
You don't deserve respect.
 You deserve to be put into
 prison for 30 years to life.

1041
01:10:46,610 --> 01:10:49,613
I understand how hard it is
 for you to accept the fact...

1042
01:10:49,646 --> 01:10:51,948
That I've been telling you
 the truth all along.

1043
01:10:51,981 --> 01:10:55,885
You know, I don't know
 what it is that you want,

1044
01:10:55,919 --> 01:10:59,923
but whatever it is--
 money or fame--
 you're not gonna get it.

1045
01:10:59,956 --> 01:11:03,627
I have known 
 a lot of painters who've 
 turned into con men.

1046
01:11:03,660 --> 01:11:05,329
Hell, I knew robert trotter,

1047
01:11:05,362 --> 01:11:09,733
and I was there when we 
 caught him red-handed 
 and he confessed,

1048
01:11:09,766 --> 01:11:13,537
and I saw him sweat
and fall apart the same way
I'm gonna see you...

1049
01:11:13,570 --> 01:11:15,905
Get down on your knees
 and sweat blood.

1050
01:11:15,939 --> 01:11:19,008
I've sweated enough,
 detective murphy.

1051
01:11:19,042 --> 01:11:22,812
My work,
 my art is my sweat.

1052
01:11:22,846 --> 01:11:26,883
That's the price I've paid
 for being who I am.
 That's my pain.

1053
01:11:26,916 --> 01:11:30,887
And your pain is that you dont
 dare to allow yourself
 to believe in miracles,

1054
01:11:30,920 --> 01:11:34,724
because if you did,
 that skeptical little world
 you live in would be destroyed

1055
01:11:34,758 --> 01:11:38,795
Excuse me. What was
 your reaction to the savaging
 you received from the critics?

1056
01:11:38,828 --> 01:11:41,998
Yes, well, they have
 their opinion,
 and I have mine.

1057
01:11:42,031 --> 01:11:45,535
Do you still claim
 that you're the one
 and only vincent van gogh?

1058
01:11:45,569 --> 01:11:47,704
Yes, of course.

1059
01:11:47,737 --> 01:11:51,608
Believe it or not, 
 for better or worse, 
 I am who I am,

1060
01:11:51,641 --> 01:11:55,812
and as an artist,
 I'm also my own critic.

1061
01:11:55,845 --> 01:11:59,349
Sometimes I hate
 what I've done,
 and I paint over it.

1062
01:11:59,383 --> 01:12:01,351
Oh. Any of these
 painted over?

1063
01:12:01,385 --> 01:12:03,487
These here?
 No, no.

1064
01:12:03,520 --> 01:12:08,024
But a long time ago,
 there was one I did
 called head of girl.

1065
01:12:08,057 --> 01:12:11,595
I hated it. 
 I painted over it.

1066
01:12:11,628 --> 01:12:16,099
It started out
 as picture of a young, little
 blond girl with curly hair...

1067
01:12:16,132 --> 01:12:19,102
In a bright red bonnet
 and a violet scarf...

1068
01:12:20,169 --> 01:12:23,807
But it--
 it looked too, uh, tsk...

1069
01:12:23,840 --> 01:12:25,809
M-m-masculine.

1070
01:12:25,842 --> 01:12:27,911
So I--

1071
01:12:27,944 --> 01:12:31,715
I took out the bonnet
 and painted out
 the rest of it,

1072
01:12:31,748 --> 01:12:35,018
the scarf, and called it
 head of boy.

1073
01:12:35,051 --> 01:12:37,153
I just saw it.

1074
01:12:37,186 --> 01:12:40,590
Here. "Van gogh's
 head of boy.

1075
01:12:40,624 --> 01:12:45,161
Owned by the morganstern 
 family in hyannis port, 
 Massachusetts, since 1915."

1076
01:12:45,194 --> 01:12:48,865
Gabe, we have to go there
and convince them to let us
have this painting x-rayed.

1077
01:12:48,898 --> 01:12:52,869
Whoa. Wait a minute.
 My expenses in this case
 are beginning to add up.

1078
01:12:52,902 --> 01:12:56,773
Gabe, if the girl's scarf
 and bonnet show up...

1079
01:12:56,806 --> 01:13:00,844
Under the face of the boy
 in an x-ray, the results
 could be earth-shattering.

1080
01:13:00,877 --> 01:13:03,713
[ Kathy ] 
 What more proof 
 would anybody need?

1081
01:13:12,055 --> 01:13:17,494
But, Mr. Morganstern, there is
 no way that an x-ray could
 possibly harm your painting.

1082
01:13:17,527 --> 01:13:21,498
They do it all the time.
 I give you my word.
He's absolutely right, sir.

1083
01:13:21,531 --> 01:13:23,933
Do you know about
 the van gogh painting
 called winter ?

1084
01:13:23,967 --> 01:13:26,836
A beautiful work, winter. 
 What about it?

1085
01:13:26,870 --> 01:13:28,972
When they
x-rayed it,

1086
01:13:29,005 --> 01:13:31,608
they found a woman
at a spinning wheel
underneath it.

1087
01:13:31,641 --> 01:13:35,445
Surely if he's painted over
 winter, there must be others
 that he's painted over too.

1088
01:13:35,479 --> 01:13:40,049
While you two were en route
 to come see me, I got
 another request about this.

1089
01:13:40,083 --> 01:13:45,121
Do either of you by any chance
 know detective murphy of the
 LA.P.D. Art theft detail?

1090
01:13:45,154 --> 01:13:47,791
- holy cow!
 - she seems convinced...

1091
01:13:47,824 --> 01:13:50,594
That the x-ray will prove
 once and for all...

1092
01:13:50,627 --> 01:13:53,797
That your vincent
 is a con man and a fraud,

1093
01:13:53,830 --> 01:13:56,900
and I would like 
 the matter settled.

1094
01:14:03,973 --> 01:14:09,212
There it is.
 It's right below
 the surface.

1095
01:14:09,245 --> 01:14:11,848
Painting of 
 a young girl.

1096
01:14:11,881 --> 01:14:13,883
It's actually there.

1097
01:14:13,917 --> 01:14:17,186
[ Morganstern ] 
 Quite incredible.

1098
01:14:17,220 --> 01:14:19,789
[ Murphy ] 
 He tricked us.

1099
01:14:19,823 --> 01:14:23,527
How can it be a trick? Only
 vincent van gogh would know
 what he painted under there.

1100
01:14:23,560 --> 01:14:26,763
There's got to be some logical
 rational explanation.

1101
01:14:28,665 --> 01:14:32,235
Suppose van gogh
 wrote about this...

1102
01:14:32,268 --> 01:14:34,871
In one of his letters
 to his brother theo.

1103
01:14:36,205 --> 01:14:38,842
And suppose the impostor
 read it...

1104
01:14:38,875 --> 01:14:41,545
And unfortunately
 we walked into his trap.

1105
01:14:41,578 --> 01:14:43,913
All I know is
 there's her hat
 and her scarf.

1106
01:14:43,947 --> 01:14:46,883
You can even see
 her curly hair.

1107
01:14:48,251 --> 01:14:50,854
No. No.

1108
01:14:50,887 --> 01:14:53,289
[ Male newscaster ] 
 Head of boy.
 Head of girl.

1109
01:14:53,322 --> 01:14:57,794
Scholars say van gogh 
 never left a clue about this 
 in any of his letters.

1110
01:14:57,827 --> 01:14:59,796
Experts are 
 more baffled than ever.

1111
01:14:59,829 --> 01:15:02,632
The new vincent. 
 Is he really van gogh?

1112
01:15:02,666 --> 01:15:04,934
The investigation continues.

1113
01:15:04,968 --> 01:15:08,605
It's time we went
 to france together, kathy.
 Oh. What for?

1114
01:15:08,638 --> 01:15:11,675
To get the paintings
 that I hid there
 over a hundred years ago.

1115
01:15:11,708 --> 01:15:15,211
What? Wha--
 what paintings did you hide?

1116
01:15:15,244 --> 01:15:17,781
Some of my very best,
 and they're well-hidden.

1117
01:15:17,814 --> 01:15:21,951
It's highly unlikely that
 anyone has ever discovered
 them. [ Giggles ]

1118
01:15:23,687 --> 01:15:26,222
Exactly where
in france are they?
 In a crypt...

1119
01:15:26,255 --> 01:15:29,593
Inside a church
 at a place called arles.

1120
01:15:29,626 --> 01:15:32,095
Would you recognize the church
 if you saw it again?

1121
01:15:32,128 --> 01:15:35,298
Since when did you
 become so inquisitive?
 All of these questions.

1122
01:15:35,331 --> 01:15:37,667
I'm sorry, but if
 leonardo da vinci
 were alive...

1123
01:15:37,701 --> 01:15:40,169
And he told you he had hidden
 some of his best paintings,

1124
01:15:40,203 --> 01:15:42,271
you would want to know
 where they were too.

1125
01:15:42,305 --> 01:15:47,644
Leonardo? I don't think so.
 His style is so stiff
 and confining.

1126
01:15:47,677 --> 01:15:49,579
Take the mona lisa, 
 for example.

1127
01:15:49,613 --> 01:15:51,981
No, don't put down
 the mona lisa.

