01:30:43,906 --> 01:30:46,208
my dear 
 kathy madison,

1358
01:30:46,241 --> 01:30:49,144
and with all my love.

1359
01:30:49,177 --> 01:30:51,213
[ Clinking ]

1360
01:30:58,153 --> 01:31:00,823
Kathy?

1361
01:31:00,856 --> 01:31:04,627
I hope that you can find
 someone that you can
 love and marry...

1362
01:31:04,660 --> 01:31:06,595
And have children with.

1363
01:31:06,629 --> 01:31:08,531
Well, I've already
 fallen in love...

1364
01:31:10,132 --> 01:31:12,067
With you.

1365
01:31:16,238 --> 01:31:20,609
Kathy, nothing would make me
 happier than to marry you.

1366
01:31:20,643 --> 01:31:25,548
But it wasn't meant to be. 
 It wasn't fated.

1367
01:31:25,581 --> 01:31:28,717
Well, what does fate
 have to do with it?

1368
01:31:28,751 --> 01:31:30,919
Everything.

1369
01:31:30,953 --> 01:31:35,057
When the flowers
 called me back to this world,
 it was only for a short while.

1370
01:31:35,090 --> 01:31:37,760
No, the flowers
 didn't call you back.

1371
01:31:37,793 --> 01:31:40,863
The flowers
 can't make decisions.
 The flowers don't have souls.

1372
01:31:40,896 --> 01:31:42,898
Don't say that.
 They do.

1373
01:31:42,931 --> 01:31:45,100
They most certainly
 do have souls.

1374
01:31:51,940 --> 01:31:54,777
I have a confession to make.

1375
01:31:54,810 --> 01:31:57,746
I've squandered 
 a little money today.

1376
01:31:57,780 --> 01:32:00,182
What did you buy?

1377
01:32:00,215 --> 01:32:03,819
I happen to have it
 right here.

1378
01:32:03,852 --> 01:32:06,254
It's a new yellow hat.
 It's for you.

1379
01:32:06,288 --> 01:32:08,824
Oh. For me?

1380
01:32:08,857 --> 01:32:11,594
- there you go.
 - wait.

1381
01:32:13,261 --> 01:32:15,664
- beautiful.
 - [ Chuckles ]

1382
01:32:23,338 --> 01:32:25,307
[ Laughing ]

1383
01:32:26,942 --> 01:32:30,813
[ Sighs ]
 Hello.
 Hello.

1384
01:32:30,846 --> 01:32:34,983
I never cared about
 growing old before.

1385
01:32:35,017 --> 01:32:37,285
But now I think
 it would be lovely...

1386
01:32:37,319 --> 01:32:40,623
To watch my hair
 becoming white,

1387
01:32:40,656 --> 01:32:43,859
to walk with a cane,
 arm in arm with you.

1388
01:32:43,892 --> 01:32:47,229
You have many years
 before you become old,
 vincent.

1389
01:32:48,296 --> 01:32:52,801
You have many years, kathy.
 Not me.

1390
01:32:52,835 --> 01:32:55,237
Kathy, darling,

1391
01:32:55,270 --> 01:32:57,740
the sea is calling out to me.

1392
01:32:59,307 --> 01:33:02,277
Listen.
 It's whispering my name.

1393
01:33:05,681 --> 01:33:08,283
I don't hear anything
 but you, vincent.

1394
01:33:17,159 --> 01:33:20,629
I'll always
 be with you, kathy.

1395
01:33:20,663 --> 01:33:25,300
When you Miss me,
 look into one of my paintings.

1396
01:33:25,333 --> 01:33:30,038
I will be right there,
 gazing into your eyes.

1397
01:33:30,072 --> 01:33:34,877
Margot said that the sea
 and the waves would take me
 away on the hundredth day.

1398
01:33:48,824 --> 01:33:50,793
What are you doing?

1399
01:33:52,027 --> 01:33:53,395
Vincent?

1400
01:33:53,428 --> 01:33:56,364
Vincent?

1401
01:33:56,398 --> 01:33:59,434
Vincent, no!

1402
01:33:59,467 --> 01:34:01,804
Vincent, 
 come back!

1403
01:34:01,837 --> 01:34:04,272
Vincent, 
 I love you!

1404
01:34:07,242 --> 01:34:09,311
Vincent!

1405
01:34:09,344 --> 01:34:12,715
Vincent, I love you!
 Please!

1406
01:34:14,282 --> 01:34:16,852
Vincent, I love you.

1407
01:34:18,320 --> 01:34:21,223
Vincent.
 [ Sobbing ]

1408
01:34:21,256 --> 01:34:24,159
[ Crying ]

1409
01:34:27,963 --> 01:34:29,998
No.

1410
01:34:44,379 --> 01:34:46,915
Well?

1411
01:34:46,949 --> 01:34:50,753
The museums have made
 their determination.

1412
01:34:52,254 --> 01:34:55,791
It's the conclusion
 of five museums.

1413
01:34:55,824 --> 01:34:58,226
Our conclusion is...

1414
01:34:58,260 --> 01:35:01,129
That they were not painted
 in this century.

1415
01:35:02,430 --> 01:35:07,035
Most likely they were created 
 between 1886...

1416
01:35:07,069 --> 01:35:09,437
And 1890.

1417
01:35:09,471 --> 01:35:12,440
They are genuine works
 by vincent van gogh.

1418
01:35:15,778 --> 01:35:18,180
Vincent did return.

1419
01:35:37,099 --> 01:35:39,868
[ Kathy narrating ] 
 His yellow hat was all 
 that was ever found.

1420
01:35:41,036 --> 01:35:43,872
They never found his body.

1421
01:35:43,906 --> 01:35:45,941
He had disappeared.

1422
01:35:47,742 --> 01:35:52,047
I'd never really believed him 
 when he said he only had 
 a hundred days.

1423
01:35:52,080 --> 01:35:56,018
I thought my love for him 
 would keep him here...

1424
01:35:57,385 --> 01:36:00,188
But it was just like 
 vincent said.

1425
01:36:00,222 --> 01:36:03,425
The flowers had called him 
 back into this world,

1426
01:36:03,458 --> 01:36:05,794
and the sea 
 and the waves...

1427
